
[1]ashes

   ASH'ES, n. plu. Without the singular number.

   1. The earthy particles of combustible substances remaining after
   combustion; as of wood or coal.

   2. The remains of the human body when burnt. Hence figuratively, a dead
   body or corpse.

   3. In scripture, ashes is used to denote vileness, meanness, frailty,
   or humiliation.

   I who am but dust and ashes. Gen 18.

   I abhor myself and repent in dust and ashes. Job 42.
